32:08.290 --> 32:12.080
♪ It's a long way back again ♪

32:14.080 --> 32:16.250
♪ A few left turns ♪

32:16.250 --> 32:20.250
♪ And honey, we got lost ♪

32:20.250 --> 32:24.460
♪ But I still kept
my fingers crossed ♪

32:24.460 --> 32:28.500
♪ Wish I could
take a train ♪

32:28.500 --> 32:32.170
♪ Back to us again ♪

32:32.170 --> 32:34.080
- How would you describe
your artistic process?

32:34.080 --> 32:35.580
- Well, let's see.

32:35.580 --> 32:37.290
That's changed a
lot over the years.

32:37.290 --> 32:38.920
If you'd asked me
that 15 years ago,

32:38.920 --> 32:41.790
I would have a very, very
serious answer for you.

32:41.790 --> 32:43.250
And then life happens.

32:43.250 --> 32:44.960
And, you know, now I have

32:44.960 --> 32:46.460
these two girls that
I'm trying to raise up

32:46.460 --> 32:48.710
and I have this
wonderful husband

32:48.710 --> 32:51.620
who I am working with
and writing with.

32:51.620 --> 32:53.750
And, you know,
I'm a very hands-on mom.

32:53.750 --> 32:57.210
So I got the carpool and
we got dinner every night.

32:57.210 --> 33:01.880
So my process becomes whatever
hour I can grab in-between.

33:01.880 --> 33:05.710
It's all about life that
goes into the process.

33:05.710 --> 33:07.880
I guess I could describe
it as organized chaos.

33:07.880 --> 33:09.580
(chuckles)

